From 38d89e8277b08f58696a49744bb1e9ce9ccafc3f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 6 Aug 2025 11:53:22 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Fix corruption and memory leak in
 radius_das

Currently in radius_das_receive, allocated radius_das_msg is not getting
freed, if the message is received from the unknown client. This leads to
memory leak during hwsim test case. Fix this by freeing the message even
if the message is received from a unknown client.

Note: This is fixing the changes from openWrt patch,
 * 761-shared_das_port.patch

Patch-dependency: 761-shared_das_port.patch
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/radius/radius_das.c | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/src/radius/radius_das.c
+++ b/src/radius/radius_das.c
@@ -487,7 +487,6 @@ radius_das_receive_msg(struct radius_das
 	}
 
 fail:
-	radius_msg_free(msg);
 	radius_msg_free(reply);
 }
 
@@ -555,6 +554,8 @@ static void radius_das_receive(int sock,
 
 	if (!found)
 		wpa_printf(MSG_DEBUG, "DAS: Drop message from unknown client");
+
+	radius_msg_free(msg);
 }
 
 
